comments.body:
Here is a first attempt at enabling different providers based on the artifact type of the component. One question I have is whether we should add a new artifact type such as "simple" or "command" that does not even require a tarball, or whether we should make that a special case of the "tarball" artifact type (where the id specified has a particular value such as "none" or "null"). [~jianhe] [~gsaha]

Example json:
{noformat}
{
  "name": "test1", 
  "lifetime": "3600",
  "components" : 
    [
      {
        "name": "SLEEP",
        "number_of_containers": 2,
        "artifact": {
          "id": "<path_to_tarball_in_hdfs>",
          "type": "TARBALL"
        },
        "launch_command": "sleep 3600",
        "resource": {
          "cpus": 2, 
          "memory": "1024"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "SLEEP_DOCKER",
        "number_of_containers": 2,
        "artifact": {
          "id": "<docker_image_name>",
          "type": "DOCKER"
        },
        "launch_command": "sleep 3600",
        "resource": {
          "cpus": 2, 
          "memory": "1024"
        }
      }
    ]
}
{noformat}

